IMPRESSION:


CERVICAL SPINE:
1.  Numerous bilateral neuroforaminal masses, left greater than right, slightly increased in size at C2-C3 and C4-C5.


BRACHIAL PLEXUS NEUROGRAPHY:
1.  Numerous bilateral brachial plexus intercostal peripheral nerve sheath tumors, a few of which are increased in size, including left neuroforaminal plexiform lesion at C4-C5. However, the majority are similar in size compared to prior.
2.  Similar mild asymmetric atrophy and fatty replacement of the left rotator cuff and deltoid muscle.


Images and interpretation personally reviewed by: Andrew Kilgore, MD
